Description: Cylinder seal of black steatite: perforated through the centre, bearing an incised design in two registers. The upper register contains six figures of birds and the lower register four figures of animals. The exact identity of the types of birds and animals represented is uncertain. Good condition.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl. 28, abb. 70; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit II (Wiesbaden, 1964), 1102.
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: Rev George Denis Nash
